I can see the main problem.

Your posts are not showing because your blog page is using paginator.posts, but your _config.yml does not include a pagination plugin.

Right now you have:

plugins:
  - jekyll-sitemap
But your page expects pagination to exist:

{% if paginator.posts and paginator.posts.size > 0 %}
So paginator is never being created, which means your template falls into the empty state every time.

What’s going wrong
The main issue is this:

you are using paginator.posts

but pagination is not enabled in a way Jekyll can actually use

so no posts are passed into the page

There are also a few secondary issues:

your blog hero is constrained to max-width: 760px, so it feels centered and narrow rather than properly left-aligned

you are loading search.js twice

your blog page currently has no image area in the hero

the search field and button are too soft for what you want

your site url is set to embracingauthenticity.co.uk, which is the wrong site for this project

Immediate fix for posts not displaying
The simplest fix is:

1. Stop using paginator.posts
Use site.posts instead.

Replace this:

{% if paginator.posts and paginator.posts.size > 0 %}
  <div class="acw-blog-grid" id="blogPosts">
    {% for post in paginator.posts %}
with this:

{% assign blog_posts = site.posts %}
{% if blog_posts and blog_posts.size > 0 %}
  <div class="acw-blog-grid" id="blogPosts">
    {% for post in blog_posts %}
And remove the pagination nav for now.

2. Remove this from the blog page front matter
Delete this:

pagination:
  enabled: true
  collection: posts
So the top of blog.html becomes:

---
layout: default
title: Blog
---
3. Fix your _config.yml site URL
Change:

url: "https://embracingauthenticity.co.uk"
to your actual therapist site URL.

For example:

url: "https://alexanderclivewatson.co.uk"
or whatever domain you are actively using.

